environment.model.roadusers.vehicles

Class Vehicle

  • java.lang.Object
    • environment.model.roadusers.vehicles.Vehicle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FamilySedan_Vehicle, Motorbike_Vehicle, SmallCar_Vehicle, Truck_Vehicle

    public abstract class Vehicle
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    The Vehicle class models a Vehicle which is being refilled with fuel at a fuel station.

    The Vehicle class is an abstract class which cannot be used as an anonymous class, and must be extended by another class to be usable.

    The Vehicle class provides a number of method to modify and describe the status of the Vehicle. The Vehicle class also contains the shared behaviour of every type of Vehicle i.e. every Vehicle is full when it's fuel level is equal to the size of it's tank.

    Subclasses of the Vehicle class should

    • Have a fixed physical size
    • Have a fixed fuel tank size
    • Have a fuel level
    Examples of such could be, cars, motorcycles and lorries; as each of these vehicles have, a fixed fuel tank size, a physical size and a fuel level which increases as the vehicle is being refilled.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Vehicle

        protected Vehicle(double size,
                  int tankSize)
        Create a new Vehicle object.

        Create a new Vehicle by defining a physical size to for the Vehicle object's size, and a fuel tank size as the Vehicle object's tankSize; after the initialisation the Vehicle object cannot have the size and tankSize changed.

        Provided arguments must be greater than 0, otherwise default values are:

        1. size = 0.5
        2. tankSize = 1

        Parameters:
        size - The physical size of the Vehicle.
        tankSize - The size of the tank of the Vehicle.

      • Vehicle

        protected Vehicle(double size,
                  int tankSize,
                  int fuelLevel,
                  FuelType fuelType)
        Create a new Vehicle by defining the size, tank and current fuel level.

        Initialise a Vehicle with s specified size, tankSize, fuelLevel and a fuelType.

        Provided arguments must be greater than 0 or not null, otherwise default values are:

        1. size = 0.5
        2. tankSize = 1
        3. fuelLevel = 0
        4. fuelType = FuelType.PETROL

        This constructor should be used to clone the Vehicle objects.

        Parameters:
        size - The size of the Vehicle.
        tankSize - The tank size of the Vehicle.
        fuelLevel - The current fuel level of the Vehicle.
        fuelType - The fuelType of the Vehicle.

      • getFuelLevel

        Returns:
        The current fuel level of the Vehicle.

      • fill

        public final void fill()
        Increment the Vehicle objects fuelLevel by one.

        If the Vehicle object's fuelLevel is less than the tankSize, increment the fuelLevel by one; otherwise the tank is full and cannot be filled further, which means that the fuelLevel will not be incremented as a Vehicle cannot fill it's fuel tank once it is full.

      • isFull

        public final boolean isFull()
        Check if the Vehicle has completely filled it's fuel tank.

        Check if the Vehicle the Vehicle has completely filled the fuel tank. Cannot be overridden in subclasses as every instance of Vehicle is full when the fuelLevel is equal to the tankSize.

        Returns:
        true if the fuelLevel is equal to the tankSize, otherwise return false.

      • getCurrentWorth

        public final double getCurrentWorth()
        Get the current worth of the Vehicle.

        The current worth of the Vehicle is the current cost of filling the Vehicle. The current worth of the Vehicle cannot exceed the getMaxWorth(). When the isFull() method returns true, the current worth is equal to the getMaxWorth().

        The current worth of the Vehicle is calculated as *fuelLevel.

        Returns:
        The current cost of filling the Vehicle.

      • getMaxWorth

        public final double getMaxWorth()
        Get the total worth of refilling the Vehicle.

        The max worth of a Vehicle is the cost of filling the fuel tank until it is full.

        The total worth of the Vehicle is calculated as *tankSize.

        Returns:
        The total cost of filling the Vehicle.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Check if two Vehicle objects are equal.

        For an object to equal a Vehicle object, the object must

      • Be an instance of the Vehicle class
      • Have the same size
      • Have the same tankSize
      • Have the same fuelType

Overrides:
